<h2><?php _e('Introduction','wppopup'); ?></h2>
<p><?php _e('The main WP Popup screen show all of the WP Popup you have set up, you can edit, activate / deactivate and reorder the priority of the WP Popup using this screen.','wppopup'); ?></p>
<h2><?php _e('Adding a WP Popup','wppopup'); ?></h2>
<p><?php _e('To add a WP Popup you can either click on the <strong>Add New</strong> link near the top of the page, or click on the <strong>Create New</strong> menu item in the main wppopup menu.','WP Popup'); ?></p>
<h2><?php _e('Activating / Deactivating a wppopup','wppopup'); ?></h2>
<p><?php _e('If you find that you do not need a particular WP Popup for a period of time, but want to keep it for later use, then clicking on the Deactivate link underneath the WP Popup title will ensure the WP Popup is not included in the processing.','wppopup'); ?></p>
<p><?php wppopup_helpimage('wppopupdeactivate.png'); ?></p>
<p><?php _e('You can re-activate at any time by clicking on the Activate link underneath the WP Popup title','wppopup'); ?></p>
<p><?php wppopup_helpimage('wppopupactivate.png'); ?></p>
<h2><?php _e('Ordering WP Popup','wppopup'); ?></h2>
<p><?php _e('The WP Popup are processed in the order they show in the list. As soon as a WP Popup is shown, the remainder of the WP Popup in the list are ignored. You can change the order of the WP Popup processing by clicking in the left hand column of the list and dragging the relevant WP Popup to the desired location.','wppopup'); ?></p>
<p><?php wppopup_helpimage('wppopupmove.png'); ?></p>
<h2><?php _e('Deleting WP Popup','wppopup'); ?></h2>
<p><?php _e('Once you have finished with a WP Popup you can delete it by clicking on the Delete link underneath the WP Popup title.','wppopup'); ?></p>
